FGDH Thesis LaTeX Template — Licensing
======================================

This repository is dual-licensed, and additionally bundles third-party files that
keep their own terms. Read this file first; the full legal texts are in `LICENSES/`.

1. LaTeX code  (LPPL 1.3c)
--------------------------
The template's own LaTeX source — the `fgdh-thesis` document class and its style files
(`fgdh-thesis.cls`, the deprecated `wise.cls` alias, `wiseapp.sty`, `wisetextDE.sty`,
`wisetextEN.sty`), the `template/` and `examples/` `.tex` sources, and any build
configuration — is licensed under the LaTeX Project Public License, version 1.3c or later.

  Full text: LICENSES/LPPL-1.3c.txt   (https://www.latex-project.org/lppl/lppl-1-3c/)
  SPDX-License-Identifier: LPPL-1.3c

This work has the maintenance status "maintained".

  Original author (`wise` class, 2012): Malte Helmhold, TU Dresden,
      Lehrstuhl für Wirtschaftsinformatik, insb. Systementwicklung.
  Current Maintainer: Forschungsgruppe Digital Health, Technische Universität Dresden.
  Contact (means of communication required by the LPPL):
      https://github.com/forschungsgruppe-digital-health/thesis-latex-template/issues

Per the LPPL, this is a modified/continued derived work of the original `wise` class;
changes are recorded in CHANGELOG.md. Anyone distributing a further-modified version
must comply with the LPPL (clearly identify it as modified; renaming is recommended).

2. Documentation & template content  (CC BY 4.0)
-------------------------------------------------
The accompanying prose documentation (everything under `docs/`, this repository's
README, and explanatory figures) is licensed under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International license, so it may be reused with attribution.

  Full text: LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0.txt   (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)
  SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0

Creative Commons licenses are intentionally NOT applied to the LaTeX code above
(CC recommends against using CC licenses for software).

3. Third-party bundled files  (own terms — NOT covered by 1 or 2)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
The bundled BibTeX styles `wisenat.bst`, `wisealpha.bst`, and `wisenatnosc.bst`
(K.F. Lorenzen's DIN 1505 `natdin`/`alphadin` styles, derived from Oren Patashnik's
standard BibTeX styles) are third-party works whose original copyright and conditions
are retained verbatim in the files. See THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md for the full attribution
and terms. They are redistributed here under their original terms and are not relicensed.

When in doubt about a specific file, the notice in that file's own header governs.
